body:
hi all,

i installed owncloud on my computer on windows 8 with bitnami (owncloud 4.5.5-0 + apache 2 + mysql).

i use caldav4j, a java api, to talk to owncloud.

i am able to create calendar collection, but i can't have other thing than an "unnamed" collection.
if i look at http://localhost/owncloud/remote.php/caldav/calendars/username/, i can see that :
```
	..	[parent]		
	default calendar	collection, calendar		
	unnamed	collection, calendar		
	unnamed	collection, calendar		
	unnamed	collection, calendar		
	unnamed	collection, calendar		
	unnamed	collection, calendar		
	unnamed	collection, calendar		
	outbox	collection, schedule outbox		2013-01-28t14:20:43+00:00
```
and if i look at source code of this page for one calendar :
```
....
<td><a href="/owncloud/remote.php/caldav/calendars/username/mycalendar">unnamed</a></td>
...
```
i concluded that the name of collection is well, but not the displayname even if i add this param in my java code during the mkcalendar definition :
```java
	@test
	public void testmkcalendar(){
		string st_path ="/owncloud/remote.php/caldav/calendars/username/mycalendar";
		mkcalendarmethod mk = new mkcalendarmethod();
		mk.setpath(st_path);

		mk.adddisplayname("mycalendar");

		try {
			basecaldavclient.executemethod(caldavcollectionmanager.gethostconfiguration(), mk);
		} catch (httpexception e) {
			e.printstacktrace();
		} catch (ioexception e) {
			e.printstacktrace();
		}

		int i_statuscode = mk.getstatuscode();
		system.out.println( (i_statuscode == caldavstatus.sc_created) ? 0 : i_statuscode);
	}
```

can someone help me solve this issue?
if i am not enough clear, please let me know and i will give more informations.

thanks a lot in advance for your time,

quentin

edit
there is the request body :
```xml
<c:mkcalendar xmlns:c="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:caldav">
    <d:set xmlns:d="dav:">
        <d:prop>
            <d:displayname>mycalendar</d:displayname>
        </d:prop>
    </d:set>
</c:mkcalendar>
```
